# restricted/.env — credentials for hub skills and MCP servers
#
# Copy this file to restricted/.env and fill in your values.
# The .env file is gitignored; this example is tracked.
#
# Run `hub.doctor check` to verify your setup, or
# `hub.doctor setup` to scaffold missing pieces.
# Full reference: docs/mcp-servers.md

# ── Required: Jira access ───────────────────────────────────
JIRA_SERVER=https://issues.redhat.com
JIRA_USER=your-kerberos-id
JIRA_TOKEN=your-jira-personal-access-token

# ── Google Workspace MCP ────────────────────────────────────
# OAuth desktop client — one client serves every machine.
# Create at: Google Cloud > APIs & Services > Credentials > OAuth Client ID (Desktop).
# Enable APIs: Calendar, Drive, Gmail, Docs, Sheets, Slides, Forms, Tasks, People.
# Step-by-step: https://github.com/solaius/ai-asset-registry/blob/main/docs/google-workspace-install-guide.md
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret
USER_GOOGLE_EMAIL=your-kerberos-id@redhat.com
OAUTHLIB_INSECURE_TRANSPORT=1

# ── Slack MCP ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Session tokens — they EXPIRE on Slack logout or session invalidation.
# Extract with: https://github.com/maorfr/slack-token-extractor
# NOTE: the extractor writes SLACK_MCP_XOXC_TOKEN / SLACK_MCP_XOXD_TOKEN;
# drop the MCP_ prefix when pasting here.
SLACK_XOXC_TOKEN=xoxc-your-session-token
SLACK_XOXD_TOKEN=xoxd-your-session-token
# Optional (defaults shown):
# SLACK_MCP_TRANSPORT=stdio
# SLACK_LOGS_CHANNEL_ID=

# ── Optional: GitHub token ──────────────────────────────────
# Used by gh CLI / scripts that read GITHUB_TOKEN.
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your-token

# ── Optional: git-crypt key location ───────────────────────
# Default shown. Override if your key file lives elsewhere.
# GIT_CRYPT_KEY=~/.git-crypt-keys/rhoai-agentic-hub.key

# NOTE: LLM-provider credentials (e.g. Claude-on-Vertex —
# CLAUDE_CODE_USE_VERTEX / CLOUD_ML_REGION / ANTHROPIC_VERTEX_PROJECT_ID)
# do NOT belong in this file: Claude Code/Cursor auth is configured
# per-user before this repo, and the hub never touches it
# (see the section-4 note in scripts/doctor.sh).

# ── Optional: rhai-customer-tracker location ────────────────
# Defaults shown. Override if your clone lives elsewhere.
# CTRACK_DIR=../rhai-customer-tracker
# CTRACK_REPO_URL=git@gitlab.cee.redhat.com:rh-ai-pm/rhai-customer-tracker.git
